body:
Please ensure you have given all the following requested information in your report.

#### Issue details
PooledEffect with non-continuous not draw at the first time after create new instance.

#### Reproduction steps/code
particle-animation.p is taken from test assets.
```
public class ParticleEditorLauncher {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        new LwjglApplication(new ApplicationAdapter() {
            private ParticleEffectPool pool;
            private Array<ParticleEffectPool.PooledEffect> pooledEffects = new Array<ParticleEffectPool.PooledEffect>();
            private SpriteBatch batch;

            @Override
            public void create() {
                super.create();
                ParticleEffect effect = new ParticleEffect();
                effect.load(Gdx.files.internal("particle-animation.p"), Gdx.files.internal(""));
                effect.setEmittersCleanUpBlendFunction(true);
                pool = new ParticleEffectPool(effect, 0, 100);
                batch = new SpriteBatch();

            }

            @Override
            public void render() {
                super.render();
                if (Gdx.input.justTouched()) {
                    ParticleEffectPool.PooledEffect pe = pool.obtain();
                    pe.setPosition(MathUtils.random(100, 300), MathUtils.random(100, 300));
                    pooledEffects.add(pe);
                }
                Gdx.gl20.glClearColor(0, 0, 0, 1);
                Gdx.gl20.glClear(GL20.GL_COLOR_BUFFER_BIT);
                batch.getProjectionMatrix().setToOrtho2D(0, 0, Gdx.graphics.getWidth(), Gdx.graphics.getHeight());
                batch.begin();
                for (int i = 0; i < pooledEffects.size; i++) {
                    ParticleEffectPool.PooledEffect effect = pooledEffects.get(i);
                    effect.draw(batch, Gdx.graphics.getDeltaTime());
                    if (effect.isComplete()) {
                        pooledEffects.removeIndex(i);
                        effect.free();
                        i--;
                    }
                }
                batch.end();
            }
        }, new LwjglApplicationConfiguration());
    }
}
```

#### Version of LibGDX and/or relevant dependencies
1.9.8

Result: first touch the particle not draw, second is ok because pooledEffect is reset. The isComplete return true after first draw of new instance of PooledEffect
Expected: new pooledEffect draw as usual.
This bug occurs on non-continuous particles in test assets. If we check continuous on particleeditor it will work ok.
Fix: 
- Call start or reset on new instanceof PooledEffect in ParticleEffectPool or call default restart after constructor on ParticleEmitter.
